    {
        "content": "<p>You'll need to write lemmas manually like <code>theorem mul_one' (x) : x * 1 = x := Group₂.mul_one  x</code> and use those</p>",
        "id": 462333487,
        "sender_full_name": "Ruben Van de Velde",
        "timestamp": 1723637972
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I see. But then, how does Lean do it with all the different structures that are defined and use this kind of notation?</p>",
        "id": 462334048,
        "sender_full_name": "Esteban Martínez Vañó",
        "timestamp": 1723638090
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I've seen a way. If I add the \" ' \" to the definition of the class, then I can have the theorems without it :)</p>",
        "id": 462334630,
        "sender_full_name": "Esteban Martínez Vañó",
        "timestamp": 1723638333
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>the way Mathlib does this is by having <code>Group</code> extend <code>Mul</code>, such that the notation already is available in the fields of <code>Group</code></p>",
